<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No">
  <Content>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" SceneNumber="1"><Text>INT. LAB – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>A cramped NEON-LIT LAB hums with servers and monitors. CABLES snake across the floor.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JESS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>Okay, one more compile and then I swear I&apos;m done touching this parser.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MARCO</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical"><Text>(leaning over her shoulder)</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>Famous last words. What happens if it sees an FDX with no slug lines?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Jess taps a key. The monitors FLASH as lines of XML scroll by.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JESS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>Then we write a bug ticket and pretend it was a feature request.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" SceneNumber="2"><Text>EXT. CITY ROOFTOP – DAWN</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The sun creeps over the skyline. A small DRONE hovers at the edge of the roof.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MARCO</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>If your script analyzer can find this scene, it can find anything.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JESS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>I&apos;m logging location, time of day, and every character per scene. The drone even gets a credit.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>The drone BEEPS and nods as if in agreement.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" SceneNumber="3"><Text>INT. EDIT BAY – DAY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Multiple MONITORS show timelines, color wheels, and script pages side by side.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RILEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>So this app of yours can highlight every line for a single character?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JESS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical"><Text>(points at the screen)</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>Yep. Pick a character, export a script just for them. Editors, actors, even casting can use it.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RILEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>Nice. Does it handle overlapping scenes and flashbacks?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>MARCO</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>We&apos;re calling that version two, so we can still ship version one.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Scene Heading" SceneNumber="4"><Text>EXT. CITY STREET – NIGHT</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action"><Text>Traffic WHOOSHES by. Jess walks, staring at a tablet running the SCRIPT ANALYZER APP.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JESS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>Scene count... four. Characters per scene... three here, two on the roof, plus one very proud drone.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>RILEY</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>And our test user?</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character"><Text>JESS</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue"><Text>Some poor developer trying to parse this FDX file.</Text></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition"><Text>CUT TO BLACK.</Text></Paragraph>
  </Content>
</FinalDraft>
